Steps:
Strategic assessment
Technical assessment
Cost benefit analysis
Risk evaluation

👉 Isse decide hota hai project start karna chahiye ya nahi.
2. Cost Benefit Evaluation Techniques
1. Payback Period
Investment recover hone ka time

2. NPV
Future cash ka present value

3. IRR
Profit percentage

👉 Inse best project choose karte hai.

3. Risk Management
Risk management ek process hai jisme risk identify, analyze aur control kiya jata hai.

Steps:
Risk identification
Risk analysis
Risk planning
Risk control

4. Network Planning (Forward & Backward)
Network diagram me activities ko show karte hai.
Forward pass → earliest time
Backward pass → latest time

👉 Critical path identify hota hai.

5. Activity Float & Critical Path
Float = extra time
Critical path = zero float activities

👉 Critical path delay hua to project delay hoga.

6. Shortening Project Duration
Methods:
Extra resources
Overtime
Parallel work

7. Monitoring and Control
